author: Unreal Engine
description:
In this session recorded at Unreal Fest Orlando 2025, the Sony Honda Mobility development team, in collaboration with Epic Games and Q-Games, presents the UI/UX for the AFEELA 1 electric vehicle. 

This presentation includes the system interface, 3D maps, and ADAS sensing visualization, and explains how the team leveraged Unreal Engine's capabilities, with a particular focus on the implementation of the newly introduced Native Map Rendering System.

To find out more about using Unreal Engine for human-machine interfaces (HMI), check out our website: unrealengine.com/hmi

title: Making the AFEELA 1 Cockpit Unreal | Unreal Fest Orlando 2025

author: Unreal Engine
description:
In this session recorded at Unreal Fest Orlando 2025, MHP—Porsche's immersive consultancy—demonstrates how their Elastic Content Platform transforms product authenticity into revenue streams. 

Automotive showrooms are evolving into verification spaces where customers confirm products are real. This shift creates new opportunities for brands ready to master authenticity at scale. 

Watch this video to learn how to maintain consumer trust while blending CGI with GenAI world-building, creating experiences where questioning authenticity becomes irrelevant.

To find out more about Unreal Engine for automotive, check out our website: https://www.unrealengine.com/en-US/uses/automotive
